      <front>
         <p rend="justify">1888? to Harding<note xml:id="ftn3-399" place="foot" n="399">ATL MS-Copy-Micro-0485-1; Undated:</note>
         </p>
      </front>
      <body>
         <p rend="end">Friday night</p>
         <p>Mr. R.C. Harding</p>
         <p>My Dear Sir</p>
         <p>Herewith “Copy”—Notes for Appx. I worked hard <hi rend="italic">yesterday</hi> &amp; got them ready to send down this mg.—<hi rend="italic">afterwards</hi> I recollected <hi rend="italic">this day</hi>, and so retained them.—</p>
         <p>You will see what I have written—some in a hurry! bad “copy” but, I hope, legible.—</p>
         <p>If you are <hi rend="italic">quite</hi> disengaged tomorrow (<hi rend="italic">Saty.</hi>) night run up—or, say, on Monday night, suit yourself: as soon now we must think for advts.—title, &amp;c.—</p>
         <p>Hope you are keeping well</p>
         <p>Yours truly</p>
         <p>W. Colenso.</p>
      </body>
  </text>
